  <prompt>Extend `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Cache/MetricsDistributedCache.cs` (the R1 R7-S7 decorator) so every cache op method (`GetAsync`, `SetAsync`, `RemoveAsync`, `RefreshAsync`) is wrapped in `try/finally`. On exception, classify via a new private `ClassifyException(Exception ex)` helper that maps to `outcome` ∈ {`timeout`, `canceled`, `connection`, `serialization`, `other`}, record a NEW `cache.failures` Counter with `outcome` + `op` dimensions, then rethrow. Counter MUST be emitted via the canonical `Sprk.Bff.Api.Telemetry.CacheMetrics` static class (post task 002) — task 001 may register on the existing instance if 002 hasn't landed yet, but MUST NOT create a second Meter instance. Pre-task-002 fallback: emit via the existing CacheMetrics instance Counter API. If task 002 has already landed, emit via the static class.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer with OpenTelemetry Metrics + .NET 8 cache decorator experience. Apply `task-execute` skill at FULL rigor.</role>
  <goal>`MetricsDistributedCache.cs` extended: try/finally on every public cache method; `ClassifyException` private helper; new `cache.failures` Counter emitted with `outcome` + `op` dimensions before rethrow. Build clean (0 errors). No existing test regressions. KQL acceptance verified at task 030 post-deploy.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>R1 R7-S7 (PR #460) wired the OTel Azure Monitor exporter and added `MetricsDistributedCache` with `cache.hits` / `cache.misses` / `cache.redis_call_duration_ms`. Senior review (DEF-007) noted there is no failure counter; Redis outages are invisible.</background>
