  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `MetricsDistributedCache.cs` end-to-end. Identify all public methods (GetAsync, SetAsync, RemoveAsync, RefreshAsync — confirm in source).</step>
    <step order="2">Read `Telemetry/CacheMetrics.cs` to confirm Counter API surface (whether `RecordFailure(outcome, op)` exists or needs to be added). If task 002 hasn't landed, may need to add a temporary Counter on the instance; if 002 has landed, emit via canonical static class.</step>
    <step order="3">Design `ClassifyException(Exception ex)` helper: `OperationCanceledException` → "canceled", `TimeoutException`/`RedisTimeoutException` → "timeout", `RedisConnectionException`/`RedisServerException`/`SocketException` → "connection", `JsonException`/`InvalidOperationException` (serialization context) → "serialization", default → "other".</step>
    <step order="4">Wrap each public method body in `try/finally`. Capture failure outcome via local var; in catch, classify + record + rethrow.</step>
    <step order="5">Verify the Counter emission point uses the SAME Meter as `cache.hits` / `cache.misses` — do NOT create a second Meter instance (anti-pattern that task 002 explicitly fixes).</step>
    <step order="6">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — 0 errors, ≤2 new warnings.</step>
    <step order="7">Run existing unit tests covering MetricsDistributedCache (if any) to confirm no regression. Skip integration if dev Redis is required.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX status 🔲 → ✅. Update current-task.md with file modified.</step>
    <step order="9">Step 9.5 quality gates: `code-review` + `adr-check`.</step>
  </steps>
